The paper deals with resource allocation and interference coordination in multicell systems, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The proposed framework involves coordination among multiple base stations and terminals, which can be seen as a system-level control problem (cs.SY). The evaluation of the proposed strategies involves processing and analyzing measured data, which can be categorized as multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) tasks.
